rComments: This professor is harsh when grading papers and exams. His expectations for answers during the time constraints of an exam are particularly onerous. The lectures are boring, with a reliance on textual quotes and class discussion rather than scholarship. He is difficult to hear (talks quickly and softly). I do not recommend this course.
He has a very good lecture structure, but as said before he's so harsh a grader it borders on unfair.

rComments: You might say he's hard, but that's because he cares about the difference between a strong argument and a weak one. His comments will make you a better writer. He is a fair and kind educator.

Objectively speaking, he's a decent professor; he knows his stuff. Having said that, he's a hard-as-hell marker, where it almost teeters on being unfair, and he's not very clear about what he expects from you.

rComments: Fantastic prof! Witty, engaging, enthusiastic and extremely approachable. Made me a better essayist. Will never get over his Beyonce reference when discussing Troilus & Cressida ;) Take ANY class with him!

Taught a Shakespeare course in the evening...which is difficult to do! He succeeded in keeping the class intrigued and showed enthusiasm. He has very good presence. Found the marking system random though.
A good, nice guy. His enthusiasm shows, and he seems to care about his students. A fair marker, and my essays improved after his class. Random fact: his office is in a completely random place.
He's pretty interesting, sarcastic at times, but he shows considerable amount of enthusiasm in the class. A good prof overall.
A well-dressed, funny, and intelligent man. And he's so young. I adored coming to his class.
